<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 20 at 9:32PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Wheeler, southeastern
Gray, northern Collingsworth and northeastern Donley Counties through
1030 PM CDT...
At 932 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles east of Lefors to 3 miles southeast of
Lake Mcclellan. Movement was east at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Shamrock, Wheeler, Mclean, New Mobeetie, Lake Mcclellan, Twitty,
Dozier, Lela, Alanreed, Kellerville and Mobeetie.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
